    "last_activity_date" : 1391091550,
    "creation_date" : 1391091550,
    "answer_id" : 21458940,
    "question_id" : 21457538,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can find all the information you need about this topic on d.android.com: <a href=\"http://developer.android.com/tools/publishing/app-signing.html#signapp\">http://developer.android.com/tools/publishing/app-signing.html#signapp</a></p>\n\n<pre><code>jarsigner -verbose -sigalg SHA1withRSA -digestalg SHA1 -keystore my-release-key.keystore\nmy_application.apk alias_name\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>One thing that cost me a few hours already, but is also mentioned in the official documentation:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>As of JDK 7, the default signing algorithim has changed, requiring you to specify the signature and digest algorithims (-sigalg and -digestalg) when you sign an APK</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
